SB 1594-2
(LC 161)
2/9/26 (CPA/ps)
Requested by Senator JAMA
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
SENATE BILL 1594
1 In line 2 of the printed bill, after the semicolon insert “amending ORS
2 180.810;”.
3 Delete lines 4 through 22 and insert:
4 “SECTION 1. ORS 180.810 is amended to read:
5 “180.810. (1) The Attorney General shall publish model policies intended
6 to limit, to the fullest extent possible consistent with state and federal law,
7 immigration enforcement at public schools, public health facilities, court-
8 houses, public shelters and other public facilities operated by a public body.
9 “(2) When the Department of Justice develops, reviews or updates
10 the model policies described in subsection (1) of this section, the de-
11 partment shall consult with the Office of Immigrant and Refugee Ad-
12 vancement.
13 “[(2)] (3) All public bodies are encouraged to implement policies based on
14 the model policies described in subsection (1) of this section.
15 “[(3)] (4) Any entity that contracts with a public body to provide services
16 related to physical or mental health, education or access to justice is en-
17 couraged to adopt policies based on the model policies described in sub-
18 section (1) of this section.
19 “[(4)] (5) The Attorney General may adopt rules to implement this
20 section.”.
